1
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:39,520
<i>Someone once told me, the logic of life,</i>

2
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,160
<i>the way everyone fights and struggles,</i>

3
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:46,280
<i>is no different</i>
<i>from big fish eating little fish.</i>

4
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:49,160
<i>It's no wonder every fish</i>

5
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:51,880
<i>keeps greedily scavenging</i>

6
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:56,760
<i>just to grow bigger and bigger.</i>

7
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,240
<i>But why does it have to be this way?</i>

8
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:03,320
<i>Who decided this?</i>

9
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:05,720
<i>Who set the rules?</i>

10
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:07,920
<i>Nature, maybe?</i>

11
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:13,960
<i>Don't tell me nature invented</i>
<i>this crazy game in the ocean.</i>

12
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,520
<i>Is it really true that every fish</i>

13
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,360
<i>has to compete, bite,</i>

14
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,840
<i>and do whatever it takes</i>
<i>to grow big just to survive?</i>

15
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:42,600
<i>Does being a small fish</i>

16
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:45,120
<i>really mean you can't enjoy life</i>

17
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:49,080
<i>in the ocean like the big fish do?</i>

18
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:03,600
Took you forever to aim. Pathetic!

19
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,240
Hey! Are you looking down on me?

20
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,800
- What are you gonna do?
- Hey!

21
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:07,960
Get lost!

22
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,280
- Hey!
- Back off!

23
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,400
- Follow him!
- Hey!

24
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,920
<i>There has to be a better way.</i>

25
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:24,400
<i>Because in the end,</i>
<i>there's always a bigger fish</i>

26
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,680
<i>ready to bite.</i>

27
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:56,440
<i>The lesson this story taught me is,</i>

28
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:59,360
<i>no matter what kind of fish you are,</i>

29
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,720
<i>don't do something that dumb,</i>

30
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:05,560
<i>because it can't possibly help you win</i>

31
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,000
<i>at the real game of life.</i>

32
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,600
This is the walkway.

33
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,720
Is this where you put your bag?

34
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,240
Hey.

35
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,520
Why aren't you replying to my friend?

36
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,200
Think you're too good?

37
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,440
Are you deaf or what?

38
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,680
- You brat!
- Hey, students!

39
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,120
Oh crap!

40
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,760
What's going on here?

41
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,560
Nothing, sir.

42
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:16,120
Risa got my shoes dirty
and wouldn't apologize.

43
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,680
But it's okay, Risa.

44
00:04:19,279 --> 00:04:20,560
I forgive you.

45
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:25,400
The exams are coming up
and you're fighting?

46
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,760
Don't you think
you should be reviewing instead?

47
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:30,520
We've studied everything, sir.

48
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:39,440
We're confident
we can answer every question.

49
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:47,400
When is Professor Golf
giving us the answers?

50
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,240
After we pay, of course.

51
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:52,040
But it has to be cash only.

52
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,640
Why? Why cash?

53
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,880
Wouldn't a transfer be easier?

54
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,840
Transfers leave a paper trail.

55
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:01,640
Professor Golf is slick.
Like he's done this a million times.

56
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:04,360
He's been selling answers
since senior Lek's year.

57
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:07,960
Got cash, get an A.
Poor? Cram your brains out.

58
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,160
Sorry, I'm rich.

59
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:14,800
- Have you started cramming yet?
- Cramming the books?

60
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,160
Cramming the answers!

61
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:19,960
Students.

62
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,600
Exams are almost here.

63
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:24,160
If you need the bathroom, go now.

64
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,320
More than 15 minutes late,

65
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,120
and the door's locked.

66
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,600
NO SMOKING

67
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,840
Want to come out and settle this?

68
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:58,800
Stressed about the exam,
so your stomach's acting up?

69
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,040
Why aren't you answering?

70
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,440
So full of yourself.

71
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,280
Stay in there too long,

72
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,760
and you'll miss the exam.

73
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,600
We're worried, you know.

74
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,720
Jane! What are you doing?

75
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,640
Phor?

76
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,880
I'm soaking wet!

77
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,920
I thought it was Risa.
I saw her heading to the bathroom.

78
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,680
I'm here.

79
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,880
Don't miss the exam. I'm worried.

80
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:44,120
Risa! Open the door!

81
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,640
Risa! This isn't funny!

82
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,920
You're gonna make us miss the exam!

83
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,360
Risa!

84
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,200
Risa! Open the door!

85
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,920
I said open the door!

86
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:03,320
Arisa, what about Jennipha and the others?

87
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,160
I don't know, sir.

88
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,760
Here we are.

89
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,120
Where have you been?

90
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,960
Do you know you almost lost
your exam eligibility?

91
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,160
How'd you get soaked like this?

92
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,240
A little accident, sir.

93
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:25,080
Alright, head to your seats.

94
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,680
Was that your doing, Risa?

95
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,720
Too bad they got away.

96
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:48,640
Don't go off plan.
Acting on impulse will ruin everything.

97
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,560
Hey, Monkey!

98
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:55,240
What now?

99
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,720
IDIOT

100
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:04,280
How dare you say that
about my lucky exam goddess?

101
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,840
Now you're picking fights, Chunky?

102
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,840
- Bully!
- Students!

103
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,320
This is an exam room.

104
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,560
And you're talking?

105
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,400
- Sorry, sir. Yes, sir.
- Stop talking!

106
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,320
Alright, everyone, start your exam.

107
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,080
Hope you fail.

108
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,880
Not a chance.

109
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:25,560
36 HOURS EARLIER

110
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,480
Hacking LINE is a little tricky.

111
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:30,680
Every time we log in,
messages pop up on the owner's device.

112
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:34,919
But this, I can handle.

113
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,240
You can handle this, Mungkorn?

114
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:39,240
Anyone could do this. Step aside.

115
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,039
I'll take it from here.

116
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,720
PROFESSOR GOLF, I'VE SENT THE MONEY
CAN I GET THE ANSWERS YET?

117
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,040
Wait, Mungkorn.

118
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,960
Don't type it that correctly.

119
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:57,680
PROFESSOR GOLF, I'VE SENT THE MONEY.
CAN I GET THE ANSWERS YET?

120
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,640
No way she'd type that perfectly.

121
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:01,960
Okay.

122
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,720
How's this? Better?

123
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,000
PROF. GOLF, I'VE PAID!
CAN I GET THE ANSWERS NOOOOW?

124
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,240
Okay.

125
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,120
PROF. GOLF, I'VE PAID!
CAN I GET THE ANSWERS NOOOOW?

126
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,240
Prof. Golf read it.

127
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,080
OK, STAT EXAM ANSWER KEY

128
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,360
Got it!

129
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,920
STAT EXAM ANSWER KEY (5).PDF, PART 2

130
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:28,000
Now we just shuffle the answers around

131
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:30,480
and send Jane the wrong key,

132
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,480
right?

133
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:39,160
I've got one request.

134
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:42,040
Can you send the answers
to everyone in the section?

135
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,760
Why would you do that?

136
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:49,240
Nobody else deserves to get screwed over.

137
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,360
Cheat the cheater.

138
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,240
Then it's not really cheating.

139
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,960
Yes!

140
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,440
<i>With this, an A is guaranteed.</i>

141
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:12,200
You think you'll remember all the answers
just because you've got the key?

142
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:18,200
Just screenshot them on the phone.

143
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,240
That's it.

144
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:21,640
Who's gonna let you
bring a phone into the exam?

145
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,080
Just watch.

146
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:26,400
I've got a hiding spot
no one will ever find.

147
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,240
TODAY

148
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,280
Shoot!

149
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,440
Come back!

150
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,000
Come back!

151
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,760
Mungkorn.

152
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:02,760
Help me.

153
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:06,120
My battery's dead.
I can't remember the answers.

154
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,640
Mungkorn!

155
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,840
Risa!

156
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,920
Help me.

157
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:23,400
My battery's dead.

158
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,720
Are you done?

159
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,640
What's going on here, Atchariya?

160
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,120
Sorry, sir.

161
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,920
Well, I mean…

162
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,080
Your zipper's down, sir.

163
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:55,360
Here.

164
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,520
I've finished the exam.
Can I hand it in now?

165
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:19,520
IDIOT

166
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,040
Can I leave now?

167
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,200
That was close.

168
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:22,920
Hiding spot?

169
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,520
Got another one? You carrying extras?

170
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:25,520
Relax.

171
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:28,040
I just forgot to charge it, that's all.

172
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,120
Relax? We almost got caught.

173
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,120
Almost caught doing what?

174
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,440
Arisa.

175
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:36,920
I need to talk to you.

176
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,360
Come to the faculty room.

177
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,560
Let's split up for now.
I'll call you later.

178
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,400
A fellow student saw you passing answers
to someone during the exam.

179
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:20,520
Really. Do you have proof, sir?

180
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,080
Proof that I cheated, I mean.

181
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:28,960
You do realize

182
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:33,040
I could have you expelled for this.

183
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,320
I know.

184
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:39,440
I also know cheating is wrong.

185
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:41,000
But money can buy a lot of things.

186
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,480
I've heard

187
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:46,720
students who buy
your private tutoring classes

188
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:50,160
say you teach really well,

189
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,560
and the material
matches the exams perfectly.

190
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:55,800
If they also join
your merit-making donations,

191
00:15:56,400 --> 00:16:01,840
they might get both good karma
and the exact answers.

192
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,800
Hey, watch your mouth!

193
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:07,480
You can't just accuse people
without proof.

194
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,400
Without any proof?

195
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:12,080
Like how you accused me just now?

196
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,840
<i>Hello, Professor!</i>

197
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,320
<i>Here's the money, sir.</i>

198
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,560
Professor.

199
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,480
If that's everything,

200
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:39,840
I'll get going now.

201
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,000
Hey, stop right there.

202
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:48,160
I also have proof

203
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:51,480
from the LINE chat where you sent
the answer key to Jennipha.

204
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,760
Your call, sir.

205
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:57,160
Keep going or call it quits.

206
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:28,640
Hello, Mungkorn.

207
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:31,280
I got the money. We'll split it tomorrow.

208
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:51,680
Hola!

209
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,800
- Hola!
- What's up?

210
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,120
What's up?

211
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,560
Chen, don't you think so?

212
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:03,640
It's like we're watching
a wildlife documentary.

213
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:06,600
A wildlife documentary? How?

214
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,480
You've watched one before, right?

215
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:15,040
It's like this.

216
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:18,120
We're watching a herd of deer
grazing peacefully,

217
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,800
but they have no idea

218
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,040
a lion

219
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:23,920
is waiting to pounce.

220
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:29,080
What's staking out dealers
got to do with a documentary?

221
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:32,960
You just don't get it.

222
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,760
<i>Code 00, all units standby for orders.</i>

223
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,360
<i>The suspects are exchanging</i>
<i>the contraband.</i>

224
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,960
Koh, I get it!

225
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,640
The drug dealers are the deer,

226
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,640
and we're the lions hunting them down.

227
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,160
Right?

228
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:57,040
<i>All units, move in.</i>

229
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,280
Hey! Cops!

230
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:03,000
- Let's go! What the hell, man?
- Not yet.

231
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:05,440
Stop! Don't move! Police!

232
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,480
I've got a way to catch the whole herd
and save it for later.

233
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:28,640
Stop! Kill the engine
and get out of the car!

234
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,280
- Ugh!
- Whoa! Hey!

235
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,000
Don't come any closer, cop!

236
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,760
Unless you want a bullet in your eye!

237
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:55,120
Oh, bro! I'm not a cop.

238
00:19:55,200 --> 00:19:56,600
I'm just

239
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:58,720
dressed like one, that's all.

240
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,360
Easy, bro. I'm here to help you.

241
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,480
Back off!

242
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:06,400
- Don't come any closer!
- Put the gun down.

243
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,800
- Take it easy. Trust me.
- I said don't come any closer!

244
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:28,880
Is he dead?

245
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:30,480
Hey.

246
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,200
Hey.

247
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:34,240
Hey.

248
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:42,040
Bro! Look!

249
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:44,760
Right through it, I told you.

250
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:46,560
You just wouldn't believe me.

251
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,600
Don't.

252
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,800
I just came to talk.

253
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,360
I won't do anything.
Look, I'm not gonna do anything.

254
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,520
Bro.

255
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:02,880
Stay calm.

256
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:04,840
Easy. We'll talk this through.

257
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,680
Bro. Hey, bro!

258
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:08,240
Bro!

259
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:19,760
Hello there, Mr. Alpha Deer.

260
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,680
Sorry, bro.

261
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:24,880
- What the hell?
- Come here.

262
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:27,080
- Come here. Stop struggling.
- Don't.

263
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,160
Let me go.

264
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:30,640
You have no idea
whose money you're messing with.

265
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:34,640
Game's over,
and you're still talking tough?

266
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:36,760
Keep talking in jail. Move.

267
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:38,240
- Move!
- Wait!

268
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,640
You said you weren't a cop.

269
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:42,400
You said you were just dressed like one.

270
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:49,400
That's strategy. Police psychology.

271
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,480
Captain.

272
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:52,920
- Yes?
- Take him back to the unit.

273
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:55,320
Beat it out of him until he confesses.

274
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,240
But…

275
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,880
don't kill him this time.

276
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,360
I don't feel like writing
another fake report.

277
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,880
- Go.
- Yes, sir.

278
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,400
- Wait.
- Alright, got something to say?

279
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,400
How about this?

280
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,720
I'll give you both the money in this bag

281
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,920
if you let me go.

282
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,000
Okay?

283
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:25,840
Trying to bribe a police officer?

284
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,440
I didn't mean it like that.

285
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:29,360
Sorry.

286
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,360
How much you got?

287
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:34,320
Huh?

288
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:36,800
I said, how much is in the bag?

289
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:42,560
Three million.

290
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:47,400
One, two, three. Okay.

291
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:52,720
Let's do this.

292
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,640
I'll confiscate this money for now.

293
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:56,720
Okay?

294
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,800
I told you, bro.

295
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:01,760
We can work something out if you want.

296
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:04,240
Hey. Next time,

297
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:06,600
if you're making a deal,
cut me in a little.

298
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:10,760
I'll pretend I didn't see anything.
But if the cops catch you,

299
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:14,040
here, just show them my business card.

300
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:17,360
I'm Lieutenant Colonel Toto.

301
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:19,040
I run this area.

302
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:20,840
- Really, sir?
- Yeah.

303
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,480
Thank you so much.

304
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,600
- I told you.
- Yes.

305
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:26,240
- We can work things out.
- Yes.

306
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:28,560
Now get going. Before I change my mind.

307
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:32,080
- Alright, I'm going.
- Good luck, bro. Safe travels!

308
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:37,400
See?

309
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:39,280
That's how you catch the whole herd

310
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,280
without chasing after them.

311
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:46,720
Koh, ease up
with the documentary stuff, will you?

312
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,960
EASY CASH

313
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,240
That's enough. Please.

314
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:06,960
I'll have the money tomorrow, I swear.

315
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,040
People say that all the time.

316
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:11,920
Not paying your debt…

317
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,240
That's not how this works.

318
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:15,360
Get up!

319
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,920
What are you gonna do to me?

320
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:26,720
This is the responsibility
I was talking about.

321
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,320
No, please! Don't!

322
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,280
My fingers! Please don't!

323
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,040
I'll take your thumb.

324
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,440
Let go! Don't!

325
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:37,560
No! Don't!

326
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:43,760
Hang on a sec.

327
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,200
Hello?

328
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:52,280
Found her?

329
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:54,080
No. Don't do anything yet.

330
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:55,520
I really care about this one.

331
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,200
I'll head over as soon as I'm done.

332
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:59,000
Yes, I promise.

333
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,920
Hello, valued customer.

334
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:11,200
Finally found you.

335
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:19,920
Keep an eye on this one, guys.

336
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:23,440
She's a real troublemaker.

337
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:31,560
- Stop!
- Stop right there!

338
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,080
Where'd she go?

339
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,520
Hey, check over there.

340
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,320
No point running yourself
into the ground, huh?

341
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:18,720
Even if you escape,

342
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:21,240
the debt doesn't disappear.

343
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:23,840
We'll find you one way or another.

344
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,520
I'm getting the money.

345
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,520
By next week, I'll pay it back.

346
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:35,280
But that's not how business works.

347
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,680
You're in debt

348
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,000
for ten million baht.

349
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:40,720
Two missed payments,

350
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,360
plus a month off the grid.

351
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:45,440
Keep this up, and the interest
will go through the roof.

352
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,480
Guys.

353
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:50,200
Go through her stuff. See what she's got.

354
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:52,680
- Give it to me!
- Let go!

355
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:55,160
- No! Let go!
- Let go! I said let go!

356
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,880
- Let go!
- Give it to me!

357
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,640
- Let go!
- Come here!

358
00:26:58,720 --> 00:27:00,120
- Let go!
- Stay still!

359
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:07,200
You said you had no money.

360
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:08,560
So what's this?

361
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,640
Give me my money back!

362
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,480
Don't sneak up on me like that.

363
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:18,760
That's not very nice.

364
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:22,640
Don't be mad at me.

365
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:24,760
If you're mad, blame your dad

366
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,880
for running out on his debt
and leaving his daughter

367
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,480
to deal with it.

368
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:32,680
Please let me take a profile picture
to send to the boss.

369
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:31,200
FIVE YEARS AGO

370
00:28:31,280 --> 00:28:32,680
Risa, are you okay?

371
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,120
I'm fine.

372
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:38,080
Okay, if you're okay, let's go.

373
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:39,600
Come on.

374
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:42,760
Dad.

375
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,600
Please tell me what's going on.

376
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,800
Are you running from someone?

377
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,280
Nothing, sweetie.

378
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,440
Let's just go.

379
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:55,080
- Can you walk?
- Yes.

380
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,720
Risa, can I have my wallet?

381
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:09,640
I thought I put it in here, Dad.

382
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:12,880
Did I drop it when I fell earlier?

383
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:14,520
I'll go check.

384
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,240
No need, sweetie.

385
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,720
Two tickets to Chiang Mai.

386
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,400
CLOSED

387
00:29:28,920 --> 00:29:30,600
Risa, wait here. I'll be right back.

388
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:44,880
- Sorry. I'm so sorry.
- Hey, you!

389
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,040
I'm so sorry.

390
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:05,760
Come on, sweetie.

391
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:09,360
We have to hurry to the platform.
Let's go.

392
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:12,600
Can you walk?

393
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,960
Here, sweetie. I got this for you.

394
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,440
Thank you, Dad.

395
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,120
Risa.

396
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:48,000
I promise.

397
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:51,880
Soon, our lives are gonna get better.

398
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:56,280
Yes.

399
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:09,800
Is this what a better life looks like?

400
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,680
Welcome, sir.

401
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:48,640
What can I get for you?

402
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:50,560
Got any recommendations?

403
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,640
I recommend the mango honey toast,

404
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:57,600
the red velvet pancakes,
or the raspberry creme brulee.

405
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,480
- For drinks, we have--
- Give me some liquor.

406
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,360
Koh.

407
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:04,720
This is a dessert cafe.
Why would you want alcohol here?

408
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:07,280
Why not? Here.

409
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:09,400
In the drawer under the counter. Go.

410
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:11,800
Why are you like this?

411
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,800
I told you not to ruin my sacred space.

412
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,440
Oh, and another thing.

413
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:21,240
If a customer walks in and sees

414
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:22,960
people drinking alcohol

415
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,960
in a dessert cafe,

416
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,240
how do you think they'll feel?

417
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:28,240
Don't worry.

418
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:30,480
Nobody'll see me, I promise.

419
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,480
Why not?

420
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:33,040
There aren't any customers.

421
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:36,200
Hey.

422
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:39,440
We just scored three million from this.

423
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:40,720
Come on, let's celebrate.

424
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:54,800
Koh.

425
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:01,560
If my cafe takes off,

426
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:05,120
we both should quit this.

427
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:08,200
Seriously. If we keep doing this,

428
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:11,440
we'll either end up dead or back in jail.

429
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:17,360
Did he take all the money?

430
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,440
I'm really sorry.

431
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:23,760
It's okay.

432
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:25,280
You're safe. That's what matters.

433
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:30,920
What about the deposit I paid
for the graphics card?

434
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:32,880
Pao, enough.

435
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:37,360
I'll find a way to get your share back.

436
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,800
Forget it.

437
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,280
We can't forget it.

438
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:44,560
We agreed we'd split everything.

439
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:46,440
It's fine.

440
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:51,080
Because we've found a new target.

441
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:58,480
Might bring in even more
than what we got from Professor Golf.

442
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:04,120
I've got a safe way to get rich.

443
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:06,920
Look.

444
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:09,760
Chen.

445
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,639
Your safe way to get rich,

446
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:13,960
do you realize people only have

447
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:16,120
a one-in-a-million chance
of winning the lottery?

448
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,360
Here.

449
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,320
Then how come people win all the time?

450
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:21,280
Luck, that's all.

451
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:22,440
Luck? What luck?

452
00:34:23,159 --> 00:34:26,600
Koh, this time, I'm serious.

453
00:34:26,679 --> 00:34:28,600
I've got the winning numbers.

454
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:33,360
GODDESS HONG FA

455
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,560
People have been following her
for dozens of draws.

456
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:37,800
She's hit the numbers
multiple draws in a row!

457
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:40,280
GODDESS HONG FA, THE GREAT GODDESS

458
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,239
That's just hype.

459
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:43,840
Listen, if she were really that accurate,

460
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,080
she wouldn't be giving out numbers.
She'd be buying them herself.

461
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,360
Here.

462
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,120
<i>Whoever seeks wealth,</i>

463
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,719
<i>whoever seeks riches…</i>

464
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:53,920
GODDESS HONG FA, THE GREAT GODDESS

465
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,199
<i>Believe in me,</i>

466
00:34:57,440 --> 00:35:01,800
<i>Goddess Hong Fa, The Great Goddess!</i>

467
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:05,440
<i>Sathu!</i>

468
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,680
- <i>Sathu!</i>
- What is this?

469
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:10,840
She calls herself
Goddess Hong Fa, The Great Goddess.

470
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:12,240
Goddess Hong Fa?

471
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:15,560
It's just a plain old scam.

472
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:18,000
Pretending to be a spirit medium,
giving out lottery numbers,

473
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,320
scamming people.

474
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,520
People still fall for this stuff?

475
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:23,720
Don't underestimate it.

476
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,400
Hey, watch this.

477
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:27,960
And your life will never be the same.

478
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:31,120
You've never checked her out before.
Watch this.

479
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:34,040
- Five tickets, 30 million!
- <i>Goddess Hong Fa,</i>

480
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:36,880
<i>The Great Goddess!</i>

481
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:40,800
<i>Sathu!</i>

482
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:43,680
<i>Sathu!</i>

483
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:46,360
- <i>Sathu!</i>
- Chen, are you crazy?

484
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,440
How can you believe this?

485
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,280
Hey, don't underestimate my goddess!

486
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,880
She's a scam goddess.

487
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:53,840
Even scams like this
can pull in millions a month.

488
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:56,400
- Huh? Millions?
- Sathu!

489
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,560
Yeah.

490
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:01,640
Otherwise, these so-called mediums
wouldn't be popping up everywhere.

491
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:02,560
Fine.

492
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,880
I'll show you

493
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:07,280
just how fake this is.

494
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,680
Ridiculous.

495
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:13,480
Hurry. The Goddess is here.

496
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:22,240
I'm here.

497
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,400
- Sathu!
- Sathu!

498
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:27,160
Whoever wants wealth,

499
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:29,960
whoever wants riches,

500
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,960
believe in me,

501
00:36:34,720 --> 00:36:39,040
Goddess Hong Fa, The Great Goddess!

502
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:42,720
- Sathu!
- Sathu!

503
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:45,560
So what's your plan, Mungkorn?

504
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:58,480
I've got a connection
with the head of the people

505
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:01,840
<i>who recruit followers into this cult.</i>

506
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:03,200
Risa.

507
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:06,600
You need to go undercover, earn the trust

508
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,920
of these so-called mediums,

509
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:11,200
and find a chance to get their money.

510
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,320
Cut! That's a wrap!

511
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:24,840
Wow, amazing.

512
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,000
Amazing.

513
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:28,120
- Applause!
- Applause!

514
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,680
Everyone, listen up.

515
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,320
Head downstairs to collect your pay.

516
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:34,920
I'm just gonna change real quick,
then head down and pay everyone.

517
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,680
- Go.
- Yeah, clap for yourselves.

518
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:40,400
Go ahead.

519
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:43,480
Next. Step right up.

520
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:46,320
Hey, when I post the clip,

521
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:48,960
- make sure you like and share it.
- Got it.

522
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,480
- Thanks a lot.
- Alright.

523
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:53,360
- No problem.
- Pay him 300 baht. Thanks so much.

524
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:54,560
Next.

525
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:57,840
- I'm Risa.
- Last one.

526
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,520
You're the last one.

527
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,720
Sign here and take your money. Go ahead.

528
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,840
- Here. Thanks a lot.
- Thank you.

529
00:38:03,920 --> 00:38:05,640
- Alright, you can go.
- Well, I mean…

530
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:08,000
You already got paid.
Why are you still standing there?

531
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:10,760
Yes, I'm leaving now.

532
00:38:12,440 --> 00:38:13,280
Whoa, Gao.

533
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:14,840
- I mean…
- Hey!

534
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:17,560
Quit hemming and hawing.

535
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:20,120
Just spit it out already.
Quit dragging this out. It's annoying.

536
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:22,640
I just wanted to know,

537
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:26,560
who came up with the name
"Goddess Hong Fa" for this cult?

538
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,440
- Why do you wanna know?
