805
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:09,240
to our front men,
the ones helping us with the plan.

806
00:54:09,320 --> 00:54:11,680
They should be able to find it. See?

807
00:54:11,760 --> 00:54:13,400
The map.

808
00:54:14,440 --> 00:54:15,880
We'll scare them.

809
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:18,400
Tell them money moves fast
between accounts these days,

810
00:54:18,480 --> 00:54:20,680
but it can disappear just as fast.

811
00:54:20,760 --> 00:54:22,840
If the police investigate

812
00:54:22,920 --> 00:54:24,320
and freeze your account,

813
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:26,000
all your money's gone.

814
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:28,560
That's why you need

815
00:54:28,640 --> 00:54:30,840
a backup account on another phone

816
00:54:30,920 --> 00:54:33,480
for emergency transfers.

817
00:54:34,800 --> 00:54:37,440
Scanning is super easy.

818
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:38,440
How?

819
00:54:41,040 --> 00:54:42,800
Just scan it like this.

820
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:43,760
See?

821
00:54:43,840 --> 00:54:45,640
The money transfers instantly.

822
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:48,480
That's really easy!

823
00:54:52,160 --> 00:54:54,640
Then I'm keeping this phone.

824
00:54:54,720 --> 00:54:57,560
But what they don't know is…

825
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:02,440
we've got another phone
that's identical to theirs.

826
00:55:02,520 --> 00:55:04,520
Except this one

827
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:06,680
is linked to our bank account.

828
00:55:08,880 --> 00:55:09,680
There he is.

829
00:55:09,760 --> 00:55:11,760
- That's the cop who bumped into me.
- A cop?

830
00:55:11,840 --> 00:55:15,400
<i>That's Koh, Captain Kongkiat Kamnerdrat.</i>
<i>He's a dirty cop.</i>

831
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:17,040
How are we supposed to track him down?

832
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:19,440
<i>Where will you be traveling today, miss?</i>

833
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:22,280
You've got some nerve,

834
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:23,680
running off with my money.

835
00:55:23,760 --> 00:55:25,000
Chop off all their legs!

836
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:28,280
- Boss, no!
- Wait! Don't!

837
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:29,920
<i>Every time you say you're okay,</i>

838
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:31,560
it feels like you're hiding something.

839
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:34,560
Pao already found him,
the guy pretending to be a cop

840
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:37,520
who stole our money. He's on his trail.

841
00:56:26,680 --> 00:56:30,440
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
